# Mark binary fixture formats so Git never performs line-ending
# normalization on them. Without this, a Windows checkout with
# `core.autocrlf=true` rewrites LF bytes inside our hand-built PDF
# fixtures to CRLF, which shifts every byte after the change and
# breaks byte-exact accessor tests (e.g. embedded attachment streams
# advertised with a literal `/Length`).
*.pdf  binary
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary

# Upstream patches must stay byte-identical to what `git format-patch`
# / `git apply` expect — no autocrlf.
*.patch binary
